<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CA basic premise of Web3,=E2=80=9D <a =
href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28989079.279539/aHR0c=
HM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTItMjEvdGhlcmUt=
cy1pbnNpZGUtaW5mb3JtYXRpb24taW4tc2VjLWZpbGluZ3M_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDkwODIyX01PTkV=
ZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09Mj=
IwOTA4JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB914bf1bc" i=
temprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"co=
lor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; b=
order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: =
#ccc;">  I once wrote</a>, =E2=80=9Cis that every product is simultaneously=
 an investment opportunity=E2=80=9D:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you sign up for a Web3 social n=
etwork or chat room or trading venue or let=E2=80=99s-buy-the-Constitution =
lark, you will get some of that project=E2=80=99s tokens, which will entitl=
e you to use the project=E2=80=99s app or exchange or Constitution, and whi=
ch will give you some notional say in the decentralized governance of the p=
roject. Also the tokens will appreciate in value if the project takes off a=
nd more people want to use it. It=E2=80=99s as if being an early user of Fa=
cebook or Uber also automatically made you a shareholder of Facebook or Ube=
r, and when those services got huge you got rich.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This has good points and bad points:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The good thing is that=C2=A0Web3 and c=
rypto have solved the cold-start problem for network-effects businesses. It=
 is hard to build a social network or a marketplace or a ride-sharing app o=
r lots of other businesses, because those businesses are useful mainly if t=
hey have a lot of users, so they are not very useful for their=C2=A0<em>fir=
st=C2=A0</em>users.=C2=A0But if you add a crypto token, the first users get=
 the most tokens, so they stand to get the richest, so there is a lot of in=
centive to join early =E2=80=94=C2=A0which means that lots of people join q=
uickly and it=C2=A0becomes<em> </em>useful.=C2=A0=E2=80=9CThe basic idea,=
=E2=80=9D=C2=A0Andreessen Horowitz partner <a href=3D"https://link.mail.blo=
ombergbusiness.com/click/28989079.279539/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9jZGl4b2=
4vc3RhdHVzLzE0NDQwNzIzNzQ3OTg2NzU5NzA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa9c50108" it=
emprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"col=
or: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bo=
rder-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #=
ccc;"> Chris Dixon</a>=C2=A0once tweeted,=C2=A0is that =E2=80=9Cearly on du=
ring the bootstrapping phase when network effects haven=E2=80=99t kicked in=
, [you] provide users with financial utility via token rewards to make up f=
or the lack of native utility.=E2=80=9D</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: =
5px;">The bad thing is that every project is simultaneously a Ponzi scheme,=
 and it is hard to know if people are using the project because they get ut=
ility out of it or because they hope to dump their tokens on future suckers=
.</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I will not belabor this =E2=80=94=C2=A0we=E2=
=80=99ve <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28989079.=
279539/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDEt=
MTkvd2FzaGluZy13ZWIzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA5MDgyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1=
haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDkwOCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW=
9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB301ff79e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" item=
scope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorat=
ion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00000=
0; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  talked</a> about =
it <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28989079.279539=
/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTItMjEvdG=
hlcmUtcy1pbnNpZGUtaW5mb3JtYXRpb24taW4tc2VjLWZpbGluZ3M_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDkwODIyX=
01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rl=
cm09MjIwOTA4JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC914bf=
1bc" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">  extensively</a> a few times before =E2=80=94=C2=A0but I do f=
eel like I have to mention Helium? Helium is, famously, The One Real Web3 T=
hing. =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/289=
89079.279539/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAyMi8wMi8wNi90ZWNobm9sb2d5L2=
hlbGl1bS1jcnlwdG9jdXJyZW5jeS11c2VzLmh0bWw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB23ca702b=
" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D=
"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px=
; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-colo=
r: #ccc;"> Maybe There's a Use Case for Crypto After All</a>,=E2=80=9D was =
the headline of the New York Times article about it in February. Helium is =
a decentralized network of wireless hotspots for internet-of-things devices=
 like, for some reason, online mousetraps (?). From that Times article:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Helium, which was founded in 2013, didn=E2=80=
=99t start off as a crypto company. Its founders originally tried to build =
a long-range, peer-to-peer wireless network the old-fashioned way =E2=80=94=
 by persuading people and businesses to set up hot spots and stringing them=
 together. But they struggled to get enough participants, and the network s=
talled.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Frank Mong, Helium=E2=80=99s chief operating o=
fficer, told me that the company was running out of money in 2017 when an e=
ngineer suggested, during an all-hands Scotch-drinking session, that more p=
eople might be willing to set up hot spots if they could earn cryptocurrenc=
y by doing it.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThat incentive model, powered by cryp=
to, actually made sense in this case,=E2=80=9D Mr. Mong said.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So the company tore up its old business model =
and settled on a new one. Instead of building its network itself, Helium wo=
uld make it fully decentralized and let users build it themselves by buying=
 and connecting their own hot spots. Participants would be paid in crypto t=
okens, and they=E2=80=99d get to vote on proposed ideas for changes to the =
network. If the price of those tokens rose, they=E2=80=99d make even more m=
oney, and set up even more hot spots.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The new model, which was released in 2019, wor=
ked like a charm. Crypto fans raced to set up Helium hot spots and start ge=
nerating crypto tokens.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Great stuff. Helium <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28989079.279539/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9s=
aXJvbi9zdGF0dXMvMTU1MTczODU5OTI1NDc3Mzc2NQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBdfb68c6=
f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;"> ran into controversy</a> in July, which led to=C2=A0founder A=
mir Haleem=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28=
989079.279539/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9hbWlyaGFsZWVtL3N0YXR1cy8xNTUyMDExM=
jQxMzc5NDAxNzI4/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBdfd4c092" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" i=
temscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">tweeting the inc=
redible statistic</a> that the network =E2=80=9Cgenerates around $2M/mo in =
fees,=E2=80=9D but that most of that is from =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://li=
nk.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28989079.279539/aHR0cHM6Ly9kb2NzLmhlbGl=
1bS5jb20vYmxvY2tjaGFpbi90cmFuc2FjdGlvbi1mZWVzLw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBdf=
f82d33" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;">Hotspot onboarding fees</a>,=E2=80=9D and only about $6,500=
 per month comes from data fees. Roughly 99.7% of Helium=E2=80=99s revenue =
comes from new users joining; roughly 0.3% comes from people actually using=
