r should regulate it.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">He is right =
to worry: Lots of crypto stuff is scammy, or at least risky and under-discl=
osed, so as a consumer protection matter the SEC should demand more disclos=
ure and fewer scams.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand, if you are an ambitious fin=
ancial regulator who wants to regulate crypto, you have to regulate crypto!=
 You have to=C2=A0put in the work! You have to sit down to try to understan=
d how the crypto market operates, what investors need to know, and what is =
required to encourage useful=C2=A0capital formation. You have to write <em>=
rules=C2=A0</em>that anyone can read and that=C2=A0create some plausible pa=
th for how crypto developers can register their tokens and how exchanges ca=
n trade them. And then you have to focus your enforcement efforts on actual=
 consumer protection, going after the crooks instead of just the people who=
 are naive enough to walk into your office.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you don=E2=80=99t do that, then, what? Then=
 the US will not be a leader in crypto innovation, is the traditional answe=
r, and US investors will not have access to all the great crypto projects. =
As a consumer protection matter, I can see why Gensler might find this answ=
er dumb. Crypto prices have crashed, and I suspect Gensler thinks that a lo=
t of these projects are scams anyway, and so missing out on them might be b=
roadly good for US investors.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Still I do not understand the game here. Gensl=
er=E2=80=99s posture seems like a massive bet against crypto ever being imp=
ortant.=C2=A0His message is basically =E2=80=9CI should be the main regulat=
or of crypto, and as the main regulator my plan is mostly to ban it.=E2=80=
=9D That=E2=80=99s not, abstractly, an insane posture: That=E2=80=99s more =
or less the view that the US Drug Enforcement Agency takes toward cocaine, =
for instance. (Or the view that <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/28989079.279539/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2Fyd=
GljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDktMjQvY2hpbmEtZGVlbXMtYWxsLWNyeXB0by1yZWxhdGVkLXRyYW5zYWN0=
aW9ucy1pbGxlZ2FsLWluLWNyYWNrZG93bj9jbXBpZD1CQkQwOTA4MjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1=
fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjA5MDgmdXRtX2=
NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB00a6a17b" itemprop=3D"St=
oryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;=
 text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-=
color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  Chin=
a takes toward crypto</a>, for that matter.) But most of the people who are=
 jockeying to be the main regulator of=C2=A0crypto want to regulate a thriv=
ing ecosystem; they want it to be big, and they want to be in charge of it.=
 Gensler wants to be in charge of it and have it be irrelevant and cumberso=
me and slow-moving.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That=C2=A0<em>might=C2=A0</em>be a good pitch,=
 now, in the crypto winter, when so many crypto stories are about people lo=
sing their life savings to unregulated scams. But it is not going to appeal=
 to anyone in the crypto industry, and I don=E2=80=99t think it=E2=80=99s g=
oing to appeal to the politicians who are interested in crypto and who are =
<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28989079.279539/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cuY29pbmRlc2suY29tL3BvbGljeS8yMDIyLzA4LzAzL3VzLXNlbmF0ZS1iaWxsL=
XdpbGwtZ2l2ZS1jZnRjLWNyeXB0by1tYXJrZXQtb3ZlcnNpZ2h0LWJ1dC1kb2VzbnQtc2F5LWhv=
dy1tdWNoLw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB4187c269" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsc=
ope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoratio=
n: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000;=
 border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> writing their own le=
gislation</a> to decide who should regulate it. Gensler=E2=80=99s posture i=
s that he should be in charge of writing the rules for crypto, but not writ=
e them. I don=E2=80=99t see how that can work.</p>
