<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Digital World Acquisition Corp., the SPAC aimi=
ng to take former President Donald Trump=E2=80=99s media company public, ad=
journed its shareholder meeting by another three hours to allow voting to c=
ontinue on delaying the merger.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The deadline for the merger is Thursday, and t=
he vote could decide the fate of a $1.3 billion cash infusion from DWAC=E2=
=80=99s public offering and Trump Media and Technology Group=E2=80=99s pote=
ntial listing on the stock market. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Digital World previously warned that the vote=
=E2=80=99s failure could result in the SPAC=E2=80=99s liquidation. More rec=
ently, DWAC CEO Patrick Orlando said he intends to initiate a =E2=80=9Cbuil=
t-in=E2=80=9D extension with a $2.8 million injection from his company and =
DWAC sponsor ARC Global Investments II.</p>
</blockquote>
